 :tx/rationale "RADICAL INSIGHT: The extractor concept generalizes far beyond programming languages. An extractor is any process that observes reality and produces datoms. The most powerful extractors may not be about code at all. Consider: (1) LLM-AS-EXTRACTOR: An AI agent reads a codebase and produces :component/* datoms with semantic understanding — not just syntactic module declarations but CONCEPTUAL components (this function implements auth, that module handles payment). No static analyzer can do this. The LLM IS the universal language extractor. (2) HUMAN-AS-EXTRACTOR: A developer runs braid observe and their observations become datoms. Humans are already extractors — we just need to recognize this. (3) RUNTIME-AS-EXTRACTOR: Instrument the running system, capture actual call graphs/code paths as :composition/* datoms. Production reality, not static approximation. (4) CONVERSATION-AS-EXTRACTOR: Parse conversation transcripts (design sessions, code reviews, standup notes) and extract decisions, intentions, constraints as datoms. The conversation IS data. These aren't future-state dreams — they're natural extensions of an architecture where the store is the universal bus."
